{"id": "d8ce61ff-3396-476e-81cd-959daca0e5ee", "value": "Raid or assault by ships upon a terrestrial location, typically a settlement or town, which may involve a terrestrial incursion and damage to buildings and/or capture of people. It is distinct from a battle or naval skirmish."}

{"id": "105e01a5-5b08-4f1d-9b3e-5c45b45130fb", "value": "For example chronic liver disease, inflammatory bowel disease, weight loss, liver transplant and other related illnesses."}

{"id": "bc6db26b-e969-4bd0-852e-673793f0d950", "value": "Depicting the nature and arrangement of strets and buildings within a built-up or urban area. For views within a singel street use STREET SCENE."}

{"id": "32126d0d-9fb9-4348-a01a-41da9cbcfdd2", "value": "Urban road or open space with typical activity, traffic and pedestrians. Double indexing may be appropriate with e.g. TRADE AND COMMERCE or CONSTRUCTION."}

{"id": "3dcfc113-d12e-4486-8707-025a36ff24e9", "value": "Engagement between any combination of warship, privateer, or commercial vessel in a time of war but not itself a battle. Such skirmishes may precede or follow naval battles."}

{"id": "2d3f1107-14f2-47d6-990b-63ce14fae5fd", "value": "For example tumors, leukemia, bone/ breast/ colon/ prostate cancer, Hodgings Lymphoma/ Disease, oral/ throat cancer, melanoma, ovarian and pancreatic cancer and other related illnesses."}

{"id": "5e78318c-71cf-4192-a107-62025895606d", "value": "For example, spinal tumor, stroke, Alzheimers, Attention Deficit Hyperactivity Disorder (ADHD), Cerebral Palsy, Chronic Fatigue, Dementia, Distal Muscular Dystrophy, Huntingtons Disease, Multiple Sclerosis, Narcolepsy and Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder."}
{"id": "732cc319-4e55-443e-bf31-549376992258", "value": "Scenes of snowfall or lying snow."}

{"id": "ab5374d8-fb5f-4451-98a8-32d2b6f8335e", "value": "For example arthritis, club foot, back pain, amputations and loss of certain functions. Major dysfunction of a joint, reconstructive surgery, disorder of the spine, amputations, fractures of extremities and growth impairments."}

{"id": "f2acb4e3-1849-4ac0-bba8-4516eb24775b", "value": "Seaborne assault landing troops ashore with resultant fighting on land, examples being the Battle of Maldon, 991, the Normandy landings of WWII and so on."}

{"id": "07df1dfd-9ed6-4573-9276-62f08944fb75", "value": "For example allergic contact dermatitis, Barlows Syndrome, cutaneous melanoma, irritant contact dermatitis, MRSA infection, mummification and other related illnesses."}

{"id": "ce4ff8b5-020e-4c25-84c1-fc4e41d3b819", "value": "For example mood disorders, agoraphobia, anxiety, bipolar disorder, chronic depression, eating disorders, dissociative identity disorder, multiple personality disorder, obsessive-compulsive or paranoid personality disorder and schizophrenia."}
{"id": "23b78e4e-3aa6-4048-8069-b545ef1519a3", "value": "Combined physical and mental health difficulties or conditions."}

{"id": "a09f709f-4e2c-4588-aeec-a28b4b3d3919", "value": "Movements of men, munitions, and supplies in support either of naval manoeuvres and engagements or of terrestrial troop movements at home and abroad."}
